Prompts
-------

[username@machinename <pwd>]# this is the prompt for root user

[username@machinename <pwd>]$ this is the prompt for regular user

------------------------------------------------------------
How to see if I'm able to connect to internet on my Linux box

[root@localhost ~]# nslookup google.com
Server:		192.168.23.2
Address:	192.168.23.2#53

Non-authoritative answer:
Name:	google.com
Address: 216.58.197.46
------------------------------------------------------------
To check the IP address

[root@localhost ~]# ifconfig 
eth0      Link encap:Ethernet  HWaddr 00:0C:29:E6:5E:3B  
          inet addr:192.168.23.129  Bcast:192.168.23.255  Mask:255.255.255.0
          inet6 addr: fe80::20c:29ff:fee6:5e3b/64 Scope:Link
          UP BROADCAST RUNNING MULTICAST  MTU:1500  Metric:1
          RX packets:125 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 frame:0
          TX packets:88 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 carrier:0
          collisions:0 txqueuelen:1000 
          RX bytes:10793 (10.5 KiB)  TX bytes:8032 (7.8 KiB)
------------------------------------------------------------
To see if yum has the pkg to be installed

[root@localhost ~]# yum info git
Loaded plugins: fastestmirror, refresh-packagekit, security
Determining fastest mirrors
 * base: centos.mirrors.estointernet.in
 * extras: centos.mirrors.estointernet.in
 * updates: centos.mirrors.estointernet.in
Available Packages
Name        : git
Arch        : x86_64
Version     : 1.7.1
Release     : 10.el6_10
Size        : 4.6 M
Repo        : updates
Summary     : Fast Version Control System
URL         : http://git-scm.com/
License     : GPLv2
Description : Git is a fast, scalable, distributed revision control system with an
            : unusually rich command set that provides both high-level operations
            : and full access to internals.
            : 
            : The git rpm installs the core tools with minimal dependencies.  To
            : install all git packages, including tools for integrating with other
            : SCMs, install the git-all meta-package.
------------------------------------------------------------
To install git

yum -y install git
------------------------------------------------------------
To verify the installation

[root@localhost ~]# rpm -qa | grep --color "git"
fprintd-pam-0.1-22.git04fd09cfa.el6.x86_64
git-1.7.1-10.el6_10.x86_64
------------------------------------------------------------
